  As you&#39;ve seen in this article, you can use switch statements to make a number of valid C programs which are extremely difficult to understand.  You can even take this further by embedding case labels inside statement expressions which produce truly next-level hard to understand code that can cause a variety of subtle problems.  As we&#39;ve seen above, this includes compiler crashes, compiler hangs, and subtly broken executable code.  If you commit enough of these to your code base, it is sure to get you fired!
